div.div: Enhance DNA component definitions and parsing; add support for modified bases and hydrogen bonding in constants and tests.
Enhance documentation with comprehensive API reference, developer guide, and contributing guidelines; update README for clarity and feature expansion.

Refactor structure imports and cleanup JAX modules
Updates structure import path to be more explicit and removes empty JAX-related modules that are no longer needed.
Adds pybind11 dependency for upcoming C++ integration work.

Implement comprehensive DNA data processing and feature extraction modules
- Added DNADataProcessor class for processing DNA sequences and structures, including one-hot encoding, GC content calculation, k-mer extraction, and positional features. - Introduced MSAFeatures, TokenFeatures, and StructureFeatures classes for structured feature representation in batch processing. - Developed FeatureExtractor class for extracting various features from DNA sequences, including k-mer frequencies, structural features, and complexity metrics. - Created ModelConfig and GlobalConfig classes for managing model configurations and parameters. - Implemented CovalentBondCleaner and MolecularScorer classes for cleaning covalent bonds and scoring molecular structures, respectively. - Added sterics module for detecting clashes and optimizing molecular structures based on steric interactions.

Implement inter-chain bond handling and structure cleaning in the pipeline
- Added inter_chain_bonds.py to manage polymer-ligand and ligand-ligand bond extraction. - Introduced functions to retrieve bond atom arrays and filter bonds based on specified criteria. - Enhanced pipeline.py to integrate inter-chain bond features into the data processing workflow. - Developed structure_cleaning.py to prepare PDB structures for training, including filtering and cleaning operations. - Implemented mechanisms to handle leaving atoms and manage bond types effectively. - Added error handling for data integrity checks during processing.
